				<row>
					<cell>
						<p>
							<persName ref="#ehri_et_rubinstyn_marta">Rubinstyn</persName>
						</p>
						<p>
							<persName ref="#ehri_et_rubinstyn_marta">Marta</persName>
						</p>
					</cell>
					<cell>
						<p><date when="1906-09-15">1906</date></p>
						<p><date when="1906-09-15">15/IX</date>
							<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/776252/belzyce.html">Bełżyce</placeName></p>
					</cell>
					<cell>Self-educated</cell>
					<cell><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2867714/munich.html">Neu Freimann</placeName></cell>
					<cell>Married</cell>
				</row>
			</table>
			<p>Surname from first <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">husband</term>: <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_zigelman_marta">Zigelman, Marta</persName></p>
			<p>Testimony taken by <persName ref="#ehri_et_mamet_p">P. Mamet</persName>, <date when="1946-08-04">4.8.1946</date></p>
			<p>Liquidation of the Jews of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/776252/belzyce.html">Bełżyce</placeName></p>
			<p>Until the outbreak of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080" type="subject">war</term> in <date
					when="1939">1939</date>, I lived in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublin</placeName>. In fall <date
					when="1940">1940</date>, all Jews were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject"
					>deported</term> from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublin</placeName> by the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> and settled in the villages surrounding <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublin</placeName>. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">deported</term> Jews would be taken on <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-940" type="subject">wagon</term>s, frequently they would be driven en
				masse on foot, very often it would happen during such a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518"
					type="subject">deportation</term> that many succumbed. I, my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822"
					type="subject">husband</term>, and my two <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject"
					>sons</term> aged 12–13 were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">deported</term> to
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765927/lubartow.html">Lubartów</placeName> near <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublin</placeName>. I tore myself <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">away</term> from the entire <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">transport</term> and went back to my home in
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublin</placeName>, and I <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hid</term> there in the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">attic</term>. My <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">husband</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">children</term> were taken to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/765927/lubartow.html">Lubartów</placeName>. My <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brother</term>, <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_veisbrod_leibush">Veisbrod Leibush</persName>, was living at that time in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/776252/belzyce.html">Bełżyce</placeName> near <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublin</placeName> – I called him on the telephone [to ask] that he should send a
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-940" type="subject">wagon</term> for me, and so I arrived in
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/776252/belzyce.html">Bełżyce</placeName>. In <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/776252/belzyce.html">Bełżyce</placeName> I gathered together a few <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term> and organized a [public] <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">kitchen</term>, where the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-519" type="subject">deportees</term> and the poor <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term> of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/776252/belzyce.html">Bełżyce</placeName> would come to eat. We <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">fed</term> around 1200 to 1500 <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term>. Also here I want to relate to what
				extent the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1181" type="subject">German regime</term> was rotten, that we
				could persuade the most important among them of anything for [the price of] <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1053" type="subject">gold or valuables</term>. Near us was <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_standartenfuehrer_stemmler">Standartenführer Stemmler</persName>, we could <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1053" type="subject">bribe</term> him with hard/heavy gold and diamonds as
				well as fabric and boots – redeeming Jews from the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject"
					>camp</term> of <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1692" type="camp">Józefów</placeName> near
					<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-565" type="camp">Pulawy</placeName>, not far from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName> – from <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">death</term>. As a result of our acquaintance with the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-873" type="subject">Jewish representatives</term>, such as <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_feltscher">Dr. Feltscher</persName>, the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-429"
					>SS</orgName> men <persName ref="#ehri_et_kranbuegel">Kranbuegel</persName> and <persName ref="#ehri_et_engel">Engel</persName>,
				who were considered the most famous <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477" type="subject">camp
					directors</term> in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName> – until <date
					when="1942">1942</date> we were able for various prices to ensure that no</p>
			<pb n="2" facs="EHRI-ET-YV3540315_02.jpg"/>

			<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term> or <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> would be established in our city
					(<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/776252/belzyce.html">Bełżyce</placeName>). Nevertheless in <date when="1942">1942</date>,
				in the eighth month, a Jewish quarter [city] was established in our town. They <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-614" type="subject">gathered</term> all the Jews from the entire
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublin</placeName> district – they deceived them and told them to
				bring everything with them – it was pitiful to see how the Jews even dragged with them wood. In this way, with us in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/776252/belzyce.html">Bełżyce</placeName> were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-614" type="subject">gathered</term> together around 9000 Jews. They
				allowed them to rest for three days – on the third day, the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-429"
					>SS</orgName> man inspector <persName ref="#ehri_et_engel">Engel</persName> entered the Jewish quarter – this was a beast in the
				form of a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">man</term> – straight away in the square
				he <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-540" type="subject">murdered</term> 700 <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term> – the rest were taken away to
					<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-41" type="camp">Bełżec </placeName>near <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/7531659/tomaszow-lubelski.html">Tomaszów</placeName>. There they <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-516" type="subject">burned</term> them in the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-501" type="subject">crematoria</term>.</p>
			<p>There remained Jews in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hiding</term>, who had <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hidden</term> in the city and the surrounding forests
				and came back after the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-550" type="subject">aktion</term> – around 600
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">persons</term>. From these <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term> a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> was created in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/776252/belzyce.html">Bełżyce</placeName> – our <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> was directed by the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-429">SS</orgName> men <persName ref="#ehri_et_engel">Engel</persName> and
					Yakab.<note place="bottom">Spelling uncertain - Vakab? Yakab?</note>
				<orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-512">The camp committee</orgName> and the police were Jews. <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">People</term> worked at hacking stones, building
				highways, for the firm Keymer. On <date when="1943-05-08">8.V.1943</date>, some of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term> from the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">murdered</term> and a few, even before this when they
				saw that a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> was created, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">fled</term> from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/776252/belzyce.html">Bełżyce</placeName> via various means. I myself left <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/776252/belzyce.html">Bełżyce</placeName> in the following way. At 3 AM I went out with my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">son</term>, who was sick with <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-493" type="subject">typhus</term>, running with him to the wires of the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term>.</p>

			<pb n="3" facs="EHRI-ET-YV3540315_03.jpg"/>

			<p>I <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">cut through</term> the wires and set out for
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName>. On <date when="1943-05-05">V.5.1943</date>, I
				arrived in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName>. The news that the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> had been decimated was brought to me
				already in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName> by my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brother</term>. I want just to mention here the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> director of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/776252/belzyce.html">Bełżyce</placeName> by the name <persName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000154">Göth</persName> – he <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">murdered</term> a few hundred <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> in the following manner – he gathered
				them all together, took them to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-747" type="subject">cemetery</term>,
				ordered the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> to undress, lined them
				up naked in a row, and, with a cruel, cold-bloodedness <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-540"
					type="subject">shot</term> them all. One young <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject"
					>boy</term>, his name was <persName ref="#ehri_et_kuropotvo">Kuropotvo</persName>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hid</term> among the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">dead</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> and came to the city the next day,
				early in the morning, covered in blood, because the bullet did not hit him, and he told me the entire story. The day after the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> were taken away, the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> director <persName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000154">Goth</persName>, who was also one of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> directors with whom we were acquainted and
				whom we would <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1053" type="subject">bribe</term>, told us, <q>I have
					taken good care of all the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> – I
					brought them all to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/761546/poniatowa.html">Poniatowa</placeName> near <placeName
						ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublin</placeName>!</q> – The young <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">boy</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_kuropotvo">Kuropotvo</persName> who avoided <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745"
					type="subject">death</term> at the hands of <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000154"
					>Göth</persName> fell during a later <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-550" type="subject"
					>aktion</term>. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children’s</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-550" type="subject">aktion</term> during which <persName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000154">Göth</persName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">murdered</term> them took place in <date
					when="1943-03">March 1943</date> in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/776252/belzyce.html">Bełżyce</placeName>. <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_rubinstyn_marta">Marta Rubinstyn</persName>.</p>
